Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:01.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did you save me?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.00,0:00:03.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought I'd teach you something
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.77,0:00:06.43,Default,,0,0,0,,about those bastards in the world of "ringers".
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.43,0:00:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Akagi Shigeru!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.12,0:00:10.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Ron
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.12,0:00:10.29,Default,,0,0,0,,If this goes on we'll lose
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.29,0:00:14.29,Default,,0,0,0,,He wants to go "all or nothing" more than anyone.\NThat's Akagi's true nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.29,0:00:18.52,Default,,0,0,0,,That is the ONLY chink through which I can stab at him.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.52,0:00:20.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll aim there.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.50,0:00:24.50,Default,,0,0,0,,4th Game\NSouth Round 2
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.40,0:00:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.80,0:00:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Kan.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.92,0:00:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Okaaay.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.16,0:00:41.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Tsumo.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.55,0:00:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh. 4 dora?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.80,0:00:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,A Haneman win.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.80,0:00:53.97,default - cyan,,0,0,0,,{\pos(967.666,124.666)}Haneman: 18,000/12,000 points dealer/non-dealer
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.00,0:00:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Game 4\NSouth Round 3
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.15,0:01:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Akagi's luck has been running near 100%
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.86,0:01:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,He's in good shape for a Tsumo win.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.86,0:01:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The wall is overflowing with Akagi's winning draws.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.80,0:01:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Ten, what do you mean to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.86,0:01:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Riichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.97,0:01:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Pon.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.55,0:02:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The opposite of 100% luck is 0% luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.46,0:02:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,your uncanny luck will be mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.90,0:02:28.03,default - cyan,,0,0,0,,{\pos(892.001,105.334)}#/tv/shows sub par subs presents
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.90,0:02:28.03,Default - white,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1672.001,1049.334)}**version**
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.48,0:02:35.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Goro Takeshi as Ten Takeshi
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.35,0:02:44.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Furukawa Yuki as Igawa Hiroyuki
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.75,0:02:52.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Yoshida Eisaku as Akagi Shigeru
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.30,0:03:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(944,125)}#/tv/shows subs: "They're better than nothing!"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.80,0:03:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,#/tv/shows subs are presented in classic Piss Yellow™
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.31,0:03:26.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(962.667,657)}Ten: Tenho-doori no Kaidanji\N(Ten: Nice guy on the path of Tenho)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.31,0:03:26.31,Default - white,,0,0,0,,{\pos(968,915.667)}Episode 4
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.46,0:03:32.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Kan.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.37,0:03:44.43,Default,,0,0,0,,With that Pon call and the new draw order, the game flow changed instantly.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.43,0:04:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Again the 7 Man
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.92,0:04:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,What a terrifying draw.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.52,0:04:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It's probably Akagi's winning tile.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.32,0:04:39.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Discard the 4 Pin or this 7 Man.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.20,0:04:43.77,Default,,0,0,0,,If I do that...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.72,0:04:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Break up his hidden triplet or nothing else.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.00,0:04:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,but now he's back to square one.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.12,0:05:39.03,Default,,0,0,0,,He's in Tenpai.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.52,0:05:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Now if only the game flow would come.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.35,0:05:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,With that
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.35,0:05:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,could even Akagi lose?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.03,0:06:06.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Without doubt Akagi's game flow has moved to Ten.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.46,0:06:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Nah. I can't hold him off forever with this hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.26,0:06:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Another one, two turns maybe, but that's probably the limit.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.72,0:06:23.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Discard the 3 Pin?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.73,0:06:27.63,Default,,0,0,0,,If he's discarding only safe tiles he should choose the 6Man.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.56,0:06:32.09,Default,,0,0,0,,But he won't do that after coming so far.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.10,0:06:36.20,Default,,0,0,0,,What will you discard, Ten?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.20,0:06:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,This character discarded a 6 Pin before
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.57,0:06:42.57,Default,,0,0,0,,despite it being a dangerous tile
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.57,0:06:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and he wasn't nervous at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.72,0:06:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,That is to say he theorized it was safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.32,0:06:53.46,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a... WALL.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.32,0:06:55.86,default - cyan,,0,0,0,,{\pos(923.427,193.235)}Wall: (壁 Kabe) A defensive strategy based on the unavailability of certain tiles.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.46,0:06:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,A 3/6 Pin wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.20,0:07:03.46,Default,,0,0,0,,That is, this guy knows the location of at least 3 of the 4 Pin or 5 Pin tiles.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.46,0:07:06.26,Default,,0,0,0,,There's one 4 Pin out.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.26,0:07:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And I've got one.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.26,0:07:13.55,Default,,0,0,0,,This guy has either 2 4Pin or 3 5Pin tiles in his hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.55,0:07:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, what's he waiting for?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.32,0:07:19.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It's likely with two 4 Pin tiles he'll aim for an Iipeikou.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.32,0:07:26.35,default - cyan,,0,0,0,,{\pos(936.001,251.667)}Iipeikou: A hand with one set of two sequences of the same numbers in the same suit. (here: 2Pin-2Pin-3Pin-3Pin-4Pin-4Pin)
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.72,0:07:24.43,Default,,0,0,0,,If he gets a 4Pin he'd be waiting for a 3Pin.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.83,0:07:38.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Pon.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.43,0:07:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Ron.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.46,0:07:49.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Tanyao. 4 Dora.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.46,0:07:51.92,default - cyan,,0,0,0,,{\pos(929.905,110.189)}Tanyao: Hand composed number tiles 2-8.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.89,0:07:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,8,000 points.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.57,0:07:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,3 7Mans, hun?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.09,0:08:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You catch on well.\NA fine read.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.20,0:08:04.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Good discards.\NDiscards that show intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.15,0:08:07.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The consecutive Red Dragon discards, and discarding the dora.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.40,0:08:11.77,Default,,0,0,0,,With this are you going to close the 9,500 point gap in the final hand?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.77,0:08:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Well then...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.60,0:08:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got some fighting spirit, don't you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.30,0:08:19.26,Default,,0,0,0,,If I play sluggishly I'll be dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.26,0:08:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Somehow, it seems like the wind is changing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.12,0:08:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,As I suspected.\NAkagi's next draw was a 7Man!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.15,0:08:37.35,Default,,0,0,0,,He would have won on his next draw.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.76,0:08:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,South Round 4\N Last Hand
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.57,0:08:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The points still stand at Akagi: 37,000 and Ten 27,500 .
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.00,0:08:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Point difference: 9,500.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.89,0:09:04.97,Default,,0,0,0,,His starting hand is bad
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.97,0:09:07.63,Default,,0,0,0,,but for Ten to pull off an upset
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.63,0:09:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Ten must get at least 5,200 points this hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.63,0:09:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Pon.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.40,0:09:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh no. For no reason they're completing their hands fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.35,0:09:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,That was a dangerous.\N He skillfully passed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.80,0:09:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Pon.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.49,0:09:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,This is another dangerous tile.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.72,0:10:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait a sec.\NAkagi's doing that on purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.92,0:10:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.92,0:10:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,If the other guys win, Ten can't take the top spot.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.89,0:10:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Akagi will throw this hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.89,0:10:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Will he deal into one of their hands?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.55,0:10:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,This guy's aiming for a White Dragon ToiToi
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.55,0:10:19.64,default - cyan,,0,0,0,,{\pos(965.333,121)}ToiToi: Hand composed of all triplets.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.15,0:10:20.09,Default,,0,0,0,,If he wins that's 5,200 points.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.09,0:10:22.09,Default,,0,0,0,,But, what to do about the dora?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.80,0:10:25.66,Default,,0,0,0,,If Akagi miscalculates and that guy has dora, it could utterly change he scoring.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.66,0:10:28.89,Default,,0,0,0,,There's even the chance of a Makura pair.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.66,0:10:31.60,default - cyan,,0,0,0,,{\pos(936,190.333)}Makura: (枕) Antique term for the single pair in a completed hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.46,0:10:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,There's one dora in the discards.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.20,0:10:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, now I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.90,0:10:39.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Is Akagi holding the remaining 3 dora tiles?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.95,0:10:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Currently, in this hand
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.20,0:10:48.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I have zero need to dwell on winning.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.52,0:10:50.52,Default,,0,0,0,,If I can't do it...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.52,0:10:53.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll have someone else tell me what to discard.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.92,0:11:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,As I expected. This dummy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.83,0:11:05.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh no.\NIf Akagi deals into that guy's hand, it's over.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.66,0:11:39.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Ron.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.43,0:11:42.43,Default,,0,0,0,,White dragon ToiToi.\N5,200 points.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.43,0:11:45.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Fuck.\NThis is what Akagi was aiming for.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.40,0:11:50.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I've won this East-South round.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.63,0:11:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And.. how is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.20,0:11:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.20,0:12:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I ALSO on that discard...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.17,0:12:03.17,Default,,0,0,0,,RON THE FUCK OUT OF YOU
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.69,0:12:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Pinhu, Ipeikou.\N2,000 points.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.70,0:12:14.70,Default,,0,0,0,,2,000?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.70,0:12:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,B-but that isn't an upset.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.40,0:12:20.89,Default,,0,0,0,,No. But look at the points.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.75,0:12:27.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Shanyu? (Playoff round)
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.75,0:12:30.88,default - cyan,,0,0,0,,{\pos(951.666,192.667)}shānyū: (西入, entering the West). An extended West round when no player can exceed 30,000 points.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.17,0:12:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Certainly top rated Akagi dealt 5,200 points into that guy's hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.00,0:12:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and with Ten winning 2,000 points, he's at 29,500.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.12,0:12:38.89,Default,,0,0,0,,No one has reached 30,000 points.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.89,0:12:42.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd expect as much from a  Kantō ringer.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.89,0:12:45.03,default - cyan,,0,0,0,,{\pos(953.667,110.999)}Kantō: The greater Tokyo area in western Japane.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.20,0:12:44.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Well judged.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.86,0:12:46.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Oi.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.35,0:12:55.77,Default,,0,0,0,,If my points in this extended round come beneath Ten
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.93,0:13:00.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll forfeit the match.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.12,0:13:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,W-what are you saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.12,0:13:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,At best you'll be helping him.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.40,0:13:05.83,Default,,0,0,0,,He's baiting you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.83,0:13:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't understand at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.80,0:13:12.26,Default,,0,0,0,,That which we're giving... and taking...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.26,0:13:16.23,Default,,0,0,0,,it isn't POINTS.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.72,0:13:19.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It's PRIDE.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.60,0:14:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,West Round 1
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.03,0:15:00.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Tsumo.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.00,0:15:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,2,000 points from everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.86,0:15:07.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Fuck yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.00,0:15:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That last moment double Ron in the previous game...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.00,0:15:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It changed the game flow.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.00,0:15:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,West Round 1\NFirst Honba.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.00,0:15:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Kan.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.50,0:15:19.50,Default,,0,0,0,,WHOOP THERE IT IS
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.26,0:15:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,4,100 points from everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.33,0:15:29.33,Default,,0,0,0,,West round 3.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.89,0:15:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Riichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.13,0:15:35.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Ron.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.76,0:15:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,8,000 points.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.30,0:15:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,West Round 4\NFinal hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.06,0:15:51.43,Default,,0,0,0,,All things considered, Ten should come top this round.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.43,0:15:54.06,Default,,0,0,0,,If Akagi can't win with a Yakuman hand,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.43,0:15:58.31,default - cyan,,0,0,0,,{\pos(946.667,187.667)}Yakuman:  The rarest and most valuable hands. 48,000/32,000 points for dealer/non-dealer.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.06,0:15:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,He can't pull of an upset.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.06,0:15:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,In the worst case Ten can play safe discards.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.26,0:16:01.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I can just glimpse victory.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.66,0:16:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,From the first the possibility of DaiSanGen disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.66,0:16:23.50,default - cyan,,0,0,0,,{\pos(912,193)}DaiSanGen, Kokusi Musou, Shousuushi etc. are all Yakuman valued hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.75,0:16:16.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Pon.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.06,0:16:24.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And with that the chance of Kokusi Musou is gone too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.89,0:16:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Kan.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.36,0:16:41.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Now shousuushii, daisuushii, and tsuuiisou are gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.63,0:16:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Pon.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.40,0:16:56.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And now even ryuuiisou is gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.86,0:17:12.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Kan.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.97,0:17:18.17,Default,,0,0,0,,With that nearly every chance at a Yakuman hand is gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.17,0:17:21.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Things are going ideally.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.03,0:17:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,No...\NThere's one avenue remaining.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.69,0:18:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Riichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.63,0:18:18.95,Default,,0,0,0,,If he's going to pull an upset, It can be nothing else.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.76,0:18:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Without doubt
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.76,0:18:27.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Akagi has a single wait SuuAnKou.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.76,0:18:30.13,default - cyan,,0,0,0,,{\pos(909.333,102.333)}SuuAnKou: 4 Hidden triplets
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.33,0:18:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,But... what is he waiting on?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.46,0:18:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Drawing an East Wind right after Akagi declares Riichi
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.40,0:18:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It's tough to discard it considering the game flow, but Ten's 4 Sou triplet is also difficult to discard...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.63,0:19:38.66,Default,,0,0,0,,We're saved.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.66,0:19:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Ten has all four in his hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.20,0:19:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It's 100% certain to not be Akagi's hidden-triple single wait tile.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.12,0:19:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Ten has all but won.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.72,0:20:07.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So. The 4Man, hunh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.35,0:20:33.95,Default,,0,0,0,,B-but that's not a SuuAnKou.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.95,0:20:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you haven't overtaken Ten's points!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.20,0:20:40.20,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.20,0:20:42.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Ahh...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.20,0:20:45.37,Default,,0,0,0,,My hidden triplets are over THERE.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.63,0:22:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Ahhh...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.86,0:22:25.52,Default,,0,0,0,,My hidden triplets are over THERE.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.26,0:22:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,First, 3 Ura-dora.\NA Haneman hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.97,0:22:51.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and with this it's 6 Ura-Dora.\NA Baiman hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.97,0:22:53.97,Default,,0,0,0,,t-that can't be.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.97,0:22:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Can he pull an upset?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.06,0:23:00.35,Default,,0,0,0,,If he turns over the same tile again, he'll have 9 Dora
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.35,0:23:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,An indesputable MATHEMATICAL Yakuman.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.35,0:23:54.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Akagi, where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.63,0:23:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I said it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.40,0:24:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If I placed lower than Ten in this Round
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.00,0:24:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I said I'd forfeit the match.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.00,0:24:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-ou can't
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.97,0:24:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for your efforts.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.09,0:24:16.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoo hoo!\NWE WON.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.50,0:24:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And now we celebrate!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.55,0:24:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Ten!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.80,0:24:30.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't had such a hot blooded match
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.37,0:24:32.37,Default,,0,0,0,,for a long, long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.09,0:24:38.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because of you
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.93,0:24:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that I wanted to come back.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.57,0:24:50.70,Default,,0,0,0,,S-saved.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.70,0:24:52.70,Default,,0,0,0,,No, but
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.70,0:24:54.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Seriously, 3 Ura-Dora?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.70,0:24:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,There's literally no chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.70,0:24:58.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You're wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.70,0:25:02.49,Default,,0,0,0,,When Akagi got up to leave
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.49,0:25:05.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You didn't hear him, did you?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.40,0:25:09.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It went as he expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.57,0:25:11.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the next tile over.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.92,0:25:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The next tile?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.83,0:25:35.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The Akagi in his prime
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.70,0:25:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Would have turned over all 3.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.12,0:25:46.52,Default,,0,0,0,,This was Akagi Shigeru's
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.52,0:25:49.69,Default,,0,0,0,,SuuAnKou "Hell" wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.43,0:25:54.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Mere chance gave me the win.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.40,0:25:58.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It could just as well have been him, maybe.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.17,0:26:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Ten. Thanks for everything.\NYou saved me.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.52,0:26:13.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Please let me return the favor somehow.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.46,0:26:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiroyuki.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.60,0:26:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop this ringer business already.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.40,0:26:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Wha?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.40,0:26:28.23,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no problem with your Mahjong ability.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.23,0:26:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,If you play a little longer
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.23,0:26:32.83,Default,,0,0,0,,If you lose your natural innocence
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.83,0:26:36.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I dunno, you just might be able to survive in this world
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.69,0:26:38.69,Default,,0,0,0,,HOWEVER
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.69,0:26:40.69,Default,,0,0,0,,just stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.12,0:26:47.43,Default,,0,0,0,,"Demons haunt the crossroads"
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.43,0:26:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,"Demons gather at the bones."
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.32,0:26:54.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(970.667,902.333)}The bones are the tiles.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.03,0:26:57.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(957.333,897)}In this underworld...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.63,0:27:01.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(962.667,865)}there are any number of evil, powerful, brilliant characters...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.49,0:27:05.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(962.667,878.333)}They gather because of the tiles.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.46,0:27:11.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(957.333,897)}The world you ought to be in
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.43,0:27:13.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(957.333,897)}it ain't this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.63,0:27:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(957.333,859.667)}I entered this damn place more than once,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.15,0:27:21.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(965.333,857)}and for me it's too late. I can't go back.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.43,0:27:26.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(954.667,811.667)}I have no choice but to live in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.80,0:27:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(954.667,809)}HOWEVER
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.26,0:27:32.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(957.333,809)}you can still turn back.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.20,0:27:38.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(957.333,907.667)}Later.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.66,0:27:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,An underground Mahjong national competition.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.72,0:27:55.57,Default,,0,0,0,,This battle isn't for everyday, normal people.カタギ
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.57,0:27:57.40,Default,,0,0,0,,This Mahjong is a struggle for life itself!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.40,0:27:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,He's done the UNTHINKABLE.
